n'AY, NOV. 13th\nich Day on the\nITY LOTS\nGreat Grounds) ij;\nVery Easy Terms\nlatever it may bring, I\nserve. ijwi\nGIBBONS NAMED\nCLUB FOUNEfER\nCardinal Assents to Plan of\nNational Catholic Community\nHouse.\nThe name of Cardinal Gibbons will\nappear as honorary founder on the\ntablet to be erected In the library\nof the National Catholic Community\nHouse, 601 E street northwest, It\nwas announced at the meeting: last\nnight of the Catholic Women's 8erv- I\nI ice Club. I\nIn a letter just received by Kev.\nLewis J. O'Hara, O. 8. P.. president of\nthe organization, the Cardinal says\ni in part:\n\"You have my cardial support for\ni the membership campaign which you!\nplan for the coming winter, and I\nassure you that 1 will be pleased to\nhave my name appear as honorary:\ni founder on the tablet to be erectcd!\nin the library of the Community\nj House.\n\"The policy of making no discrimination\nbetween Catholic and\nProtestant in the conduct of this\nj welfare center appeals strongly to\nme. and will, I am sure, bring a\nblessing on the Catholic Women's\nService Club.\"\nThe Service Club aims especially\nto provide resident club houses for\nout-of-town girls employed in the\nvarious government departments.\nDEMOCRATIC BALLOTS\nFOUND IN N. Y. SEWER\nNEW YORK, Nov. 4.?New York's\nelection is complete.\nTwenty-six balots. all voted\nI Democratic, were found in a sewer\n:on the lower East Side today.\nAssistant District Attorney Talley\nhas started an investigation.\nTu\nOFF 5\nI The Gret\n1%\nI No Strings to T\nEvery Article\nStore is Now Ofl\nent Selling Price.\nWM Off-O1\njl Formerly\n1 $4500\nII Now\nI *3375\nMen's Undershirts at\nH at less Than\nRoxford's No. 13510, a whit<\n[I ribbed cotton, now, per\nUllll garment\nRoxford's No. 12510, an ecn\nribbed cotton, now, per\nI garment\nRoxford's No. 2400, a silver i\nII shrunk, now, per\ngarment\nRoxford's No. 1420, a fine\nI Hi weight merino, now, per\ngarment\nRoxford's No. 1440. a fine, 1\n1111 merino, now, per\n